{{- define "submission-phase" -}}

--- SUBMISSION (MANDATORY - DO NOT SKIP) ---
After implementation and tests pass, you MUST submit for review:
1. Get commit SHA: git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD
2. Execute: liza submit-for-review {{.TaskID}} <SHA from step 1> --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
3. Verify confirmation: status changed to CODE_READY_FOR_REVIEW
4. Run liza await-verdict (see your TOOLS section above for loop semantics).
   On REJECTED: task is already reclaimed — read the rejection reason, fix, and resubmit.

❌ FAILURE MODE: Completing work, saying "ready for review", then exiting WITHOUT running the command.
The CLI command IS the deliverable. Work without command execution = nothing happened.
{{- end -}}
